1 onion, peeled and quartered|1
2 garlic cloves|1
thumb-sized chunk of ginger, peeled|1
red chilli|1
1 tbsp vegetable oil|1
tsp turmeric|1
1 tsp ground cumin|1
1 tsp ground coriander|1
1-2 tsp hot chilli powder (depending on how spicy you like your curry)|1
4 chicken breasts, cut into chunks|1
400g can chopped tomatoes|1
small pack coriander, chopped|1
rice, naan and mango chutney, to serve|1
STEP 1Blitz 1 quartered onion, 2 garlic cloves, a thumb-sized chunk of ginger and red chilli together in a food processor until it becomes a coarse paste.|0
Blitz 1 quartered onion, 2 garlic cloves, a thumb-sized chunk of ginger and red chilli together in a food processor until it becomes a coarse paste.|0
Blitz 1 quartered onion, 2 garlic cloves, a thumb-sized chunk of ginger and red chilli together in a food processor until it becomes a coarse paste.|0
STEP 2Heat 1 tbsp vegetable oil in a large saucepan and add the paste, fry for 5 mins, until softened. If it starts to stick to the pan at all, add a splash of water.|0
Heat 1 tbsp vegetable oil in a large saucepan and add the paste, fry for 5 mins, until softened. If it starts to stick to the pan at all, add a splash of water.|0
Heat 1 tbsp vegetable oil in a large saucepan and add the paste, fry for 5 mins, until softened. If it starts to stick to the pan at all, add a splash of water.|0
STEP 4Cook until the chicken begins to turn pale, adding a small splash of water if it sticks to the base of the pan at all.|0
Cook until the chicken begins to turn pale, adding a small splash of water if it sticks to the base of the pan at all.|0
Cook until the chicken begins to turn pale, adding a small splash of water if it sticks to the base of the pan at all.|0
STEP 5Pour in 400g can chopped tomatoes, along with a big pinch of salt, cover and cook on a low heat for 30 mins, until the chicken is tender.|0
Pour in 400g can chopped tomatoes, along with a big pinch of salt, cover and cook on a low heat for 30 mins, until the chicken is tender.|0
Pour in 400g can chopped tomatoes, along with a big pinch of salt, cover and cook on a low heat for 30 mins, until the chicken is tender.|0
STEP 6Stir through small pack of coriander and serve with rice, naan and a big dollop of mango chutney.|0
Stir through small pack of coriander and serve with rice, naan and a big dollop of mango chutney.|0
Stir through small pack of coriander and serve with rice, naan and a big dollop of mango chutney.|0
